<P><B><FONT size="+3">Tutorial for XtalEdit </FONT>(version 0.90*)</B></P>
(This is too short, and may not so good enough... We will improve it soon. Sorry...)
<BR><BR>

At first, please see <A href="indexuse.htm#Basic">Basic</A> in Usage.<br><BR>

-------------------------------------------<br>
<ol>
<li>Read in a sample LaMnO3_FullDistortion.csy1 in sample directory with File-Open.</li>
<li>Push Generator-mode0. Then it will calculate generators for space-group operations of the system.<br>
Result will appear in ResultWindow.<br>
At the same time, generators <br>
&lt;GEN&gt;<br>
 i r2z::(1/2,0,1/2) r2y::(0,-1/2,0)<br>
&lt;/GEN&gt;<br>
are added to EditWindow. These are space-group generator.</li>
<li>For example, remove three Mn sites. And push Generator-mode0.
Then atomic positions are recovered because this function see
the generators in &\lt;GEN&\gt; and complement atomic positions.</li>
<li>Run Vierwer-Rasmol. It will show crystals.
Try to modify &lt;RASMOL&gt; section so as to change view.</li>
<li>Run KKR(Akai)-export. It generate input file for AkaiKKR.</li>

</ol>
<br>
-------------------------------------------<br>
How to construct *.csy1 file from crystallogrphic data ?<br>
<A href="tut1jap.txt">a bit detailed tutorial in japanease.</A><br><BR>

<ol>
<li>Readin space-group sample from samples/TSPACE.
You need to know the space-group number.</li>
<li>Supply data to define primitive cell (and conventional cell).</li>
<li>Choose Wykoff positions. Delete not required block. 
You may have to duplicate some blocks.</li>
<li>Replace name of TYPE='name of Wykoff position' in SITE.</li>
<li>Write TYPE definition. Pushing ChkType will generate a templete.</li>
</ol>
Also you can use the samples in samples/TSPACE to learn Wykoff positions.
Then you don't need to define TYPE.

